\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  kali} : Plant up to 60 cm, usually hispid, green. Bracteoles not swollen, free. Perianth-segments stiff, usually winged, more or less spinose, with a distinct mid-vein.{\i  Coasts of Europe, northwards to} 60° 30'{\i  N}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  tragus }(L.) Nyman, {\i Consp}. 631 (1881) ({\i S. tragus} L.): Plant up to 100 cm, glabrous or hispid, yellowish. Bracteoles swollen and more or less connate at the base. Perianth-segments soft, not winged, not spinose, with obscure mid-vein.{\i  Coasts of S. Europe}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b ruthenica} (Iljin) Soó in Soó & Jáv., {\i Magyar Nov. Kez.}{\b  2:} 786 (1951) ({\i S. ruthenica} Iljin; incl. {\i S. pestifer} A. Nelson): Plant up to 100 cm, glabrous or shortly hispid, grey-green. Bracteoles not swollen, free. Perianth-segments soft, usually winged, not spinose, with obscure mid-vein. 2n = 36. {\i Throughout the range of the species, but only casual in much of the north}.
