\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. S. melitensis} Botsch.,{\i  Nov. Syst. Pl. Vasc.} ({\i Leningrad}) {\b 13:} 95 (1976). Glabrous shrub up to 100 cm, green or somewhat glaucous. Leaves up to 14 mm, linear, terete, acute, constricted at the base with hairy pulvinus. Bracts 2-9 mm, leaf-like, longer than the bracteoles and perianth; bracteoles ovate, acute. Flowers solitary. Perianth subglobose, 5-7 mm in diameter in fruit; segments ovate, obtuse, with 5 wings up to 2·5 mm. Stigmas shorter than the style. •{\i  Maltese Islands.} Si.
