\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. S. genistoides} Juss. ex Poiret in Lam.,{\i  Encycl. Méth. Bot. }{\b 7:} 294 (1806) ({\i S. tamariscifolia }Lag. pro parte). Glabrous, glaucous virgate shrub 30-50 cm; first- and second-year stems with numerous longitudinal ridges. Leaves up to 8 mm, fugacious, linear-filiform, mucronate, the uppermost scale-like. Bracts ovate-orbicular, acute, keeled, floccose on the upper surface. Perianth 10-15 mm in diameter in fruit, the segments elliptical, obtuse, the apex deflexed, 1-veined; wing reddish.{\i  S.E. Spain.} Hs.
